    <text>
        <body>       
                 
                <pb n="1"/>
            <p>To the President and Board of Trustees of<lb/> the Spanish and Portuguese Congregation of New York.<lb/></p>
            <p>Respected Gentlemen<lb/></p>
            <p>It is not an exaggeration in which<lb/> I unduly indulge&#44; when I say that Judaism<lb/> in America&#44; never stood in greater need of support<lb/> from a religious body as that which you represent&#44;<lb/> than at the present time.  The love that<lb/> you bear our ancestral religion&#44; and your own<lb/> discernment must <del>arouse</del> create in your minds&#44; serious apprehensions&#44;<lb/> regarding the maintenance of the principles&#44; which<lb/> you have uniformly upheld.  It was<lb/> a deep conviction that you would exercise a<lb/> blissful influence towards my carrying out an<lb/> undertaking aiming at the preservation of our<lb/> faith&#44; that inspired me with courage.  Nor<lb/> were my hopes ill&#45;founded&#44; for your liberal<lb/> appropriation in behalf of the Jewish Theological<lb/> Seminary proved an effectual incentive.<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>One Year&#39;s working has strengthened<lb/> my expectations that&#44; under God&#44; the institution<lb/> for which I plead may counteract the evils&#45;&#45;<lb/> <del>which</del> wrought by unscrupulous &#34;Radicalism&#34;.<lb/>  So believing and praying&#44; I ask that you<lb/> will evince again the same spirit of righteous<lb/> consideration&#44; in order that the scholars now<lb/> taught may receive the requisite aid&#44; and proceed<lb/> in the sacred studies meant to qualify them as<lb/> future instructors in the belief which we have inherited.<lb/>  To know that the sp ancient and respectable<lb/> body called &#34;the Spanish and Portuguese Con&#45;<lb/>gregation&#34; of New York&#44; has again practically<lb/> signified its approval of my efforts will occasion<lb/> heartfelt satisfaction.<lb/></p>
            <p>With the assurances of high esteem&#44; I subscribe<lb/> myself<lb/></p>
            <p>Yours very sincerely<lb/>
                S. Morais<lb/></p>
            <p>Philadelphia<lb/></p>
            <p>Tebeth 24th 5648<lb/>
                January 8th 1888<lb/></p>
            </body>
    </text>
